('8db2e822-fd5f-5f6c-92e5-d909718c2194', '6de21873-0b3a-4a85-96c8-30ec0e0d91ea', '___ am a student.', '我是一個學生。', 'I', 'He', 'She', 'You', 'I 是第一人稱單數主格代名詞。', '看到大寫 I 就想到「我」。', '2026-07-05 11:48:08', '2026-07-05 11:48:08'),
('7710076b-1168-556a-bbec-9ffbc2c61c48', '0f33ff7b-12a3-4aa9-8bf5-1535966d03f4', 'The judge ruled that the evidence presented by the lawyer was ___ and could be used in court.', '法官裁定律師提出的證據是可以接受的，且可以在法庭上使用。', 'acceptable', 'illegal', 'vague', 'obvious', 'ac- (朝向) + cept (拿/取) + -able (能夠...的) → 能夠被採納的 → 可以接受的。', '記住 accept (接受) + able (能夠...的) → 能夠被接受的 → 可以接受的。', '2026-07-06 16:39:46', '2026-07-06 16:39:46'),
('377f93c4-cf4d-5abe-9b53-c2a43887cef4', '3cbba4cd-9724-4a7a-9560-721d2429ba3b', 'The puppy is incredibly ___; it always licks my hand to show its love.', '這隻小狗非常親暱；它總是舔我的手來表達它的愛。', 'affectionate', 'aggressive', 'anxious', 'arrogant', 'affect (影響/情感) + -ion (名詞) + -ate (形容詞化) + -ive (形容詞字尾) → 充滿情感的。', 'affect 是「影響」，當情感能深刻「影響」你時，那種感覺就是 affectionate (充滿深情的)。', '2026-07-06 18:26:20', '2026-07-06 18:26:20'),
('3fdc8575-19b0-506d-b825-dc5343442390', 'da2c2fc8-b5f0-490e-b84d-b532a764c226', 'This expensive red wine has been allowed to ___ in oak barrels for ten years.', '這款昂貴的紅酒已在橡木桶中陳年了十年。', 'age', 'boil', 'melt', 'freeze', 'age 作為動詞時，表示「使成熟」或「陳年」。', '想像時間 (age) 讓酒的風味變得更醇厚。', '2026-07-06 18:52:58', '2026-07-06 18:52:58'),
('fe0ca309-2c05-5bc5-b5bc-5ed792b8510c', '9e56169e-29e0-43e1-90d8-f3e5524c73f7', 'Before the meeting starts, please make sure you have read the ___ so you know what topics will be discussed.', '會議開始前，請確保你已經閱讀了議程，以便知道將討論哪些主題。', 'agenda', 'budget', 'method', 'talent', '源自拉丁語 agere (去做/驅動)，agenda 指的是「必須去做的事情」→ 議程。', '想像會議中要討論的「待辦事項清單」→ 議程。', '2026-07-06 18:55:00', '2026-07-06 18:55:00'),
('fe169b9f-42d1-5948-a579-202c9468ec3c', '35e4495f-8a2f-454e-87c8-c4e2405747f6', 'The doctor warned the patient that consuming too many ___ drinks could lead to serious liver disease.', '醫生警告病人，攝取過多含酒精的飲料可能會導致嚴重的肝臟疾病。', 'alcoholic', 'nutritious', 'medicinal', 'refreshing', 'alcohol (酒精) + -ic (形容詞字尾，表示具有某種性質) → 含酒精的', 'alcohol (酒精) + ic (的) → 酒精的 → 含酒精的', '2026-07-06 19:41:06', '2026-07-06 19:41:06'),
('063544e7-b32c-51eb-8f6a-cc5e0b951678', '59b2e7a4-aa29-4156-9544-de3615378111', 'The little girl felt ___ after all her friends went home.', '當所有的朋友都回家後，那個小女孩感到很孤單。', 'alone', 'angry', 'hungry', 'sleepy', 'a- (處於...狀態) + lone (單獨的)', 'a (處於) + lone (單獨) → 孤單的。', '2026-07-06 20:10:50', '2026-07-06 20:10:50'),
('19976941-fb63-5c73-af9e-ea1283ec6618', 'ebe1475d-421c-46bf-bab4-b0ed6047e2f9', 'The discovery of these ancient pottery shards provides valuable information for the field of ___.', '這些古代陶器碎片的發現為考古學領域提供了寶貴的資訊。', 'archaeology', 'biology', 'geography', 'sociology', 'archaeo- (古代的) + -logy (學問/學說)', 'archaeo (古代) + logy (學問) → 研究古代遺物的學問。', '2026-07-06 23:37:03', '2026-07-06 23:37:03'),
('26b6175f-b058-57d6-bee5-784f0122f988', '9e87aeb1-33ac-4530-bb13-b40fb7a0a0a7', 'The children ran ___ the playground.', '孩子們在操場到處亂跑。', 'around', 'through', 'against', 'towards', 'a (在) + round (圓形) → 沿著圓形路徑移動。', '繞著圓形的路徑跑 → 到處、四處。', '2026-07-06 14:49:28', '2026-07-06 14:49:28'),
